g.text: Matt uses Multi-Sig-Crytpo websites to create 2 privatekeys, one on his labtop and one on his cellphone.

Matt goes to his public liabry to use Multi-sig-Crypto to combine his 2 private keys that he made earlier into a mulitsignautre crypto address along with an-other key created at the libary. He then prints out his paper wallet at the liarbary.

When Matt wants to send his crypto, he uses Multi-Sig-Crypto to sign the sending transaction independently from his cell, labtop, and the public libraies computer.The signed trsactions are trasferd via QR codes. Once signed, the transaction is broadcast to the network.
Matt can deposit crypto to this paper wallet just like any normal wallet.
